    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "1. The test tries to find a free port by starting a listener with port of 0 (OS chooses), then noting the port and closing.\r\n\r\n2. Next, it starts the local listener with a port of 0.\r\n\r\n3. Finally it starts the agent, and allocates another local port as a raw SSH connection to it.  In the failed case, the OS reused the random port from the first step for the raw SSH connection.\r\n\r\n4. Finally, we start an SSH session and ask the agent to forward the port from step 1 back to the listener in step 2.\r\n\r\nHowever, the port from step 1 is not free at that point, it is the SSH connection.  Thus when we connect to it, it speaks the SSH protocol which begins with `SSH-protoversion-softwareversion SP comments CR LF` c.f. https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4253.txt",
